{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/chromiumify-1","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><strong>Time: 30 minutes max if you already have a mobile development environment installed</strong></p>\n<h3 id=\"introduction\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#introduction\" aria-label=\"introduction permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Introduction</h3>\n<p>This is the first in a series of tutorials/blog posts about using <a href=\"https://github.com/chromiumify/chromiumify\">chromiumify</a> to create mobile and desktop applications that share code using node.js constructs. </p>\n<p>The series will give novel examples of using <a href=\"https://github.com/chromiumify/chromiumify\">chromiumify</a> with a focus on adhoc/mesh/fog network implementations.</p>\n<p>Before we get to that we will start by building the basic <strong>hello world</strong> server that is featured on the <a href=\"https://nodejs.org\">node.js</a> website and then running it on a mobile phone.</p>\n<p>The final output will look like the image below but you should get a good idea of what <a href=\"https://github.com/chromiumify/chromiumify\">chromiumify</a> can offer.\nThe source code is available <a href=\"https://github.com/chromiumify/hello-world-proj\">here</a></p>\n<p><strong>The only prerequisits are that you have a <a href=\"node.js\">node.js</a> runtime installed.</strong> </p>\n<p>{&#x3C;1>}\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/d7398/uvxPTnG.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 418px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 176.40449438202248%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Sample Hello World in an emulator\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/d7398/uvxPTnG.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/43e0d/uvxPTnG.png 178w,\n/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/526ee/uvxPTnG.png 355w,\n/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/d7398/uvxPTnG.png 418w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 418px) 100vw, 418px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3 id=\"lets-go\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lets-go\" aria-label=\"lets go permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Let's Go!!</h3>\n<p>To start lets install chromiumify</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ npm install chromiumify -g</code></pre></div>\n<p>Create a project folder </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ mkdir hello-world-proj\n$ cd hello-world-proj</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now create a folder for the chrome app. This will contain the build output for your project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ mkdir chrome-app</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then use chromiumify to generate a template project in the folder that you just created. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ chromiumify gen chrome-app</code></pre></div>\n<p>You should now be able to see the template project run</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ chromiumify run chrome-app</code></pre></div>\n<p>The above command should show this screen. </p>\n<p>{&#x3C;2>}\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4810928ef65d40bf583a8eff89181da7/b910a/EWcTOy9.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 414px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 129.7752808988764%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Initial Screen\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4810928ef65d40bf583a8eff89181da7/b910a/EWcTOy9.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4810928ef65d40bf583a8eff89181da7/43e0d/EWcTOy9.png 178w,\n/static/4810928ef65d40bf583a8eff89181da7/526ee/EWcTOy9.png 355w,\n/static/4810928ef65d40bf583a8eff89181da7/b910a/EWcTOy9.png 414w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 414px) 100vw, 414px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Now you have the base application up and running lets enhance it to host a web server.</p>\n<p>In the <strong>hello-world-proj</strong> folder install the Chrome App node.js libraries for <strong>net</strong>, <strong>http</strong>, <strong>dgram</strong> and <strong>fs</strong> using the init command.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ chromiumify init</code></pre></div>\n<p>We now need to create a browserified version of <strong>background.js</strong> to run the HTTP server.\nCreate a new folder called <strong>src</strong> at the same level as the chrome-app folder.</p>\n<p><strong>i.e. hello-world-proj/src</strong></p>\n<p>In that folder create a file called background.js and add the following code to it.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">chrome.app.runtime.onLaunched.addListener(function () {\n  chrome.app.window.create(&#39;index.html&#39;, { \n    &#39;bounds&#39;: {\n      &#39;width&#39;: 400,\n      &#39;height&#39;: 500\n    }\n  })\n})\n\nvar http = require(&#39;http&#39;);\nhttp.createServer(function (req, res) {\n  res.writeHead(200, {&#39;Content-Type&#39;: &#39;text/plain&#39;});\n  res.end(&#39;Hello World\\n&#39;);\n}).listen(1337, &#39;127.0.0.1&#39;);\nconsole.log(&#39;Server running at http://127.0.0.1:1337/&#39;);</code></pre></div>\n<p>The <strong>addListener</strong> event is used to show the main HTML page and the code below that is the simple http server mentioned in the introduction. </p>\n<p>Now we need to package this code to use in our application as follows. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ chromiumify src/background.js -o chrome-app/background.js</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now rerun the application</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ chromiumify run chrome-app</code></pre></div>\n<p>And on the screen that is displayed right click and select <strong>Inspect Background Page</strong>\n{&#x3C;3>}\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/830967a0974b3968636c991a9b5285cb/73926/ufkp3Uv.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 415px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 129.7752808988764%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Inspect Background Page\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/830967a0974b3968636c991a9b5285cb/73926/ufkp3Uv.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/830967a0974b3968636c991a9b5285cb/43e0d/ufkp3Uv.png 178w,\n/static/830967a0974b3968636c991a9b5285cb/526ee/ufkp3Uv.png 355w,\n/static/830967a0974b3968636c991a9b5285cb/73926/ufkp3Uv.png 415w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 415px) 100vw, 415px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>In the console you will see the output. </p>\n<p><strong>Server running at <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:1337/\">http://127.0.0.1:1337/</a></strong></p>\n<p>And you should be able to open up that location in a normal browser</p>\n<p>{&#x3C;4>}\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/820ee580b0a7e4c61f9ddfd2eefa892e/cc097/EejRWLG.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 394px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 55.61797752808989%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Browser Output\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/820ee580b0a7e4c61f9ddfd2eefa892e/cc097/EejRWLG.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/820ee580b0a7e4c61f9ddfd2eefa892e/43e0d/EejRWLG.png 178w,\n/static/820ee580b0a7e4c61f9ddfd2eefa892e/526ee/EejRWLG.png 355w,\n/static/820ee580b0a7e4c61f9ddfd2eefa892e/cc097/EejRWLG.png 394w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 394px) 100vw, 394px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3 id=\"well-done---you-are-now-running-node-in-a-chrome-app\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#well-done---you-are-now-running-node-in-a-chrome-app\" aria-label=\"well done   you are now running node in a chrome app permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Well Done!! - You are now running node in a Chrome App</h3>\n<p>Before we deploy this to the mobile device lets change the HTML in the app to make the sample easier to use. </p>\n<p>Open the HTML file at chrome-app/index.html and replace the content with the following</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n  &lt;a href=&quot;http://127.0.0.1:1337/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Click here to open http://127.0.0.1:1337/&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now rerun the application again</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ chromiumify run chrome-app</code></pre></div>\n<p>and clicking on the link in the app should open a browser window. </p>\n<h3 id=\"run-it-on-mobile\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#run-it-on-mobile\" aria-label=\"run it on mobile permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Run it on mobile</h3>\n<p>Now install the Google <a href=\"https://github.com/MobileChromeApps/mobile-chrome-apps/blob/master/docs/Installation.md\">Mobile Chrome App for your desired environment</a></p>\n<p>Once that is installed run </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ cca create chrome-android --link-to=chrome-app\n$ cd chrome-android\n$ cca run android --emulator</code></pre></div>\n<p>or for iOS </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ cca create chrome-ios --link-to=chrome-app\n$ cd chrome-ios\n$ cca run ios --emulator</code></pre></div>\n<p>You should now see our app launched </p>\n<p>{&#x3C;5>}\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/591e0120ed9434bb26ad532d53be4ca1/d8f62/j86AZXH.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 601px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 171.91011235955057%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Launched App\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/591e0120ed9434bb26ad532d53be4ca1/d8f62/j86AZXH.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/591e0120ed9434bb26ad532d53be4ca1/43e0d/j86AZXH.png 178w,\n/static/591e0120ed9434bb26ad532d53be4ca1/526ee/j86AZXH.png 355w,\n/static/591e0120ed9434bb26ad532d53be4ca1/d8f62/j86AZXH.png 601w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 601px) 100vw, 601px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>And clicking on the link pops a the browser window we showed at the start of the tutorial.\n{&#x3C;6>}\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/d7398/uvxPTnG.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 418px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 176.40449438202248%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Sample Hello World in an emulator\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/d7398/uvxPTnG.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/43e0d/uvxPTnG.png 178w,\n/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/526ee/uvxPTnG.png 355w,\n/static/ad4d4b13f3a892e72578fc9cfb3908a1/d7398/uvxPTnG.png 418w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 418px) 100vw, 418px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3 id=\"summary\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#summary\" aria-label=\"summary permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Summary</h3>\n<p>Now that we can run node.js services from mobile devices the next tutorial will investigate how  we can potientially discover these services in a local network scenario. </p>\n<h3 id=\"feedback\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#feedback\" aria-label=\"feedback permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Feedback</h3>\n<p>Please raise any comments or questions on this blog post in the <a href=\"https://github.com/chromiumify/hello-world-proj/issues\">issues section of the source repository</a> </p>","timeToRead":5,"excerpt":"Time: 30 minutes max if you already have a mobile development environment installed Introduction This is the first in a series of tutorials…","frontmatter":{"title":"chromiumify #1","cover":"https://unsplash.it/1280/500/?random?BoldMage","date":"2016-12-29T15:27:19.000Z","category":"tech","tags":["programming","chromeapp","javascript"],"author":"anton"},"fields":{"slug":"/chromiumify-1"}},"prev":{"excerpt":"Background Most high performance network applications today are using event based approaches. See nginx or libuv…","frontmatter":{"title":"Modular C APIs with kore.io and dotc","cover":"images/include.png","date":"2017-01-01"},"fields":{"slug":"/modular-c-apis-with-kore-io-and-dotc"}},"next":{"excerpt":"With the latest release of chromiumify you can now publish and install Chrome Apps from NPM. {<1>}node In this…","frontmatter":{"title":"chromiumify #2","cover":"https://unsplash.it/1280/500/?random?BoldMage","date":"2016-12-29"},"fields":{"slug":"/chromiumify-2"}},"authors":{"edges":[{"node":{"uid":"anton","name":"Anton Whalley","image":"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/130940?s=460&v=4","url":"http://gatsbyjs.org/","bio":""}}]}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/chromiumify-1","total":11,"prev":"/modular-c-apis-with-kore-io-and-dotc","next":"/chromiumify-2"}}}